-- Tanzania National Housing Aims to Sell $1 Billion of Bonds to Fund Project
-- B y   W i l f r e d   M w a k a l o s i
-- 2010-10-12T06:27:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/tanzania-national-housing-aims-to-sell-1-billion-of-bonds-to-fund-project.html
The Tanzania National Housing Corp.
plans to sell bonds to finance its 1.5 trillion shilling ($1
billion) real-estate development project, Director-General
Nehemiah Mchechu said.  “We are currently finalizing our plans to raise the money
and the project will start soon,” Mchechu said in an interview
with the Dar es Salaam-based  Daily News  newspaper today. He
didn’t give a timeframe for the planned sale or the amount to be
sold.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Wilfred Mwakalosi  in Dar es Salaam via Johannesburg at 
   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
